ges hereandanalysis of the changes fromAmy Remeikishere.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"entire list\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 388}, {\"ngram\": \"changes\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 399}, {\"ngram\": \"hereandanalysis\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"the changes\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 430}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A knife-wielding manwas shot dead in Sydney's south-westafter allegedly attempting to stab a police officer, who narrowly avoided \\\"catastrophic injuries\\\".\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999930516492369, \"rank\": 6.948399378440518e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A knife-wielding manwas\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 477}, {\"ngram\": \"a police officer\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 561}, {\"ngram\": \"catastrophic injuries\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day two of the NSW Labor conference took place in Sydney, where the premier,Chris Minns,announcedan end to no-ground evictions in the state.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999930516492369, \"rank\": 6.948399378440518e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Minns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Minns\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Minns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Minns\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"the premier\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 685}, {\"ngram\": \"no-ground evictions\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Legislation is due to be introduced in September.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Legislation\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 762}, {\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the same time, amotion to repeal youth bail laws and anti-protestlaws in NSW was defeated at the conference.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9504548042714054, \"rank\": 0.05212788183754729, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"amotion\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"youth bail laws\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 852}, {\"ngram\": \"protestlaws\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"the conference\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The motion also called for a charter of human rights to be enacted in the state.\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The motion\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 923}, {\"ngram\": \"a charter\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"human rights\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A rally against gendered violence was held outside the Labor conference, as part of26 rallies across the country this weekend.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1050, \"end\": 1055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A rally\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"gendered violence\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A pro-Palestine protest was also held outside of the conference in Sydney.A Palestine flag was lowered inside the conferencewhen the premier was speaking earlier this morning.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1199, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.9999994670116904, \"rank\": 5.329877031182347e-07, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A pro-Palestine protest\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"the conference\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"Sydney\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"the conferencewhen\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"the premier\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Labor delegates speak against motion to repeal youth bail and anti-protest laws Labor delegateJack Ayoub, who has previously run for the federal seat of Parkes, spoke against the motion put forward at the NSW Labor conference.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Parkes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.269098239394585e-25, \"text\": \"Parkes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Parkes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Parkes\"}, {\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Labor delegates\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"motion\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"youth bail\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-protest laws\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"the federal seat\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1485}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said that by calling for the repeal of bail and anti-protest laws, and for a charter of human rights in the same motion, this \\\"conflated\\\" the issues: Some people in this room may support the Human Rights Act, but it's not going to be achieved by conflating it with unrelated issues.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the repeal\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"bail and anti-protest laws\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"a charter\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"human rights\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"the same motion\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1650}, {\"ngram\": \"the issues\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"Some people\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"this room\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"the Human Rights Act\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"unrelated issues\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They should not have been conflated \\u2026 We cannot allow small groups of determined individuals - like Just Stop Oil in the UK and individuals that we have seen here - to cluster together with our public support and damage the causes which we ourselves want to advocate for.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7549981610030571, \"rank\": 0.3245044152502976, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"small groups\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"determined individuals\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1907}, {\"ngram\": \"Oil\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1928}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 1954}, {\"ngram\": \"our public support\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"the causes\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Steve Fraser- a retired paramedic of 41 years and member of the Health Services Union - was another Labor delegate to speak against the motion.\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999921301423, \"rank\": 7.855374099455967e-09, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2189, \"end\": 2194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a retired paramedic\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"41 years\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"member\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Noting that he had three minutes to speak, he detailed the importance of three minutes when it comes to an emergency response, and told the conference: Three minutes, delegates, can sometimes be the difference between life and death.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three minutes\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"three minutes\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2319}, {\"ngram\": \"an emergency response\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"the conference\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2383}, {\"ngram\": \"Three minutes\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"delegates\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"the difference\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2455}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Protests that randomly block streets without notice, actions and that result in the chaos that strands ambulance and emergency responders - or forces those responders to back and change and scramble to find a way around the unplanned mayhem - that's not our right.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that randomly block streets\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"notice\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2519}, {\"ngram\": \"actions\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2528}, {\"ngram\": \"the chaos\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2557}, {\"ngram\": \"ambulance and emergency responders\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2605}, {\"ngram\": \"those responders\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2634}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"the unplanned mayhem\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"our right\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Delegates, we have an obligation to speak out when things are wrong.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2802, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an obligation\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2766}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also our obligation to care [and] protect each other.\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2862, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our obligation\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This legislation has not stopped protests and rallies, look outside.\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This legislation\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"protests\", \"from\": 2896, \"to\": 2904}, {\"ngram\": \"rallies\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It prevents behaviour and thoughtless actions that cause chaos, that will cost lives.\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 3017, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"behaviour and thoughtless actions\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2977}, {\"ngram\": \"chaos\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 2994}, {\"ngram\": \"lives\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Labor anti-protest law opponents say it disproportionately affects Indigenous youth Labor delegateBradley Pigeonalso spoke in favour of the motion calling for bail laws and anti-protest laws in NSW to be repealed.\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3086, \"end\": 3096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.5800275543277266, \"rank\": 0.5852149509726076, \"text\": \"Indigenous\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 3214, \"end\": 3217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9504548042714054, \"rank\": 0.05212788183754729, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Labor anti-protest law opponents\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3051}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3165}, {\"ngram\": \"bail laws\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3187}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-protest laws\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pigeon said that as a person with Gomeroi heritage and growing up in Moree, in northern NSW, he \\\"know[s] firsthand\\\" that Indigenous youth are \\\"suffering [and] facing systematic discrimination and injustice that cannot be ignored\\\".\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3304, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moree_railway_station\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.279580118190447e-16, \"text\": \"Moree\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moree_railway_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moree_railway_station\"}, {\"begin\": 3356, \"end\": 3366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.5800275543277266, \"rank\": 0.5852149509726076, \"text\": \"Indigenous\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pigeon\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3241}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3263}, {\"ngram\": \"Gomeroi heritage\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3285}, {\"ngram\": \"northern NSW\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3326}, {\"ngram\": \"systematic discrimination\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3426}, {\"ngram\": \"injustice\", \"from\": 3431, \"to\": 3440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He argued that the state's anti-protest laws \\\"restrict our fundamental right to freedom of expression and peaceful assembly\\\" and \\\"stifle dissent\\\", and that repealing the law was \\\"essential to uphold the principles of democracy\\\".\", \"from\": 3467, \"to\": 3695, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the state's anti-protest laws\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3511}, {\"ngram\": \"our fundamental right\", \"from\": 3522, \"to\": 3543}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 3547, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"expression\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3568}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful assembly\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3590}, {\"ngram\": \"the law\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3640}, {\"ngram\": \"the principles\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3680}, {\"ngram\": \"democracy\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moving to the youth bail laws, Pigeon argued they disproportionately impact Indigenous youth and \\\"perpetuate cycles of disadvantage and incarceration\\\": These laws lead to the overrepresentation of Indigenous youth in the criminal justice system, denying them the opportunity for rehabilitation and a fair chance at a better future.\", \"from\": 3697, \"to\": 4029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3895, \"end\": 3905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.5800275543277266, \"rank\": 0.5852149509726076, \"text\": \"Indigenous\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the youth bail laws\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3726}, {\"ngram\": \"Pigeon\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 3734}, {\"ngram\": \"Indigenous youth\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3789}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"perpetuate cycles\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3812}, {\"ngram\": \"disadvantage\", \"from\": 3816, \"to\": 3828}, {\"ngram\": \"incarceration\", \"from\": 3833, \"to\": 3846}, {\"ngram\": \"These laws\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 3859}, {\"ngram\": \"the overrepresentation\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3890}, {\"ngram\": \"the criminal justice system\", \"from\": 3914, \"to\": 3941}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 3956, \"to\": 3971}, {\"ngram\": \"rehabilitation\", \"from\": 3976, \"to\": 3990}, {\"ngram\": \"a fair chance\", \"from\": 3995, \"to\": 4008}, {\"ngram\": \"a better future\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Removing these oppressive laws is crucial to ensure that all young people, regardless of their background, are given a chance to thrive and succeed and not just survive.\", \"from\": 4031, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these oppressive laws\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4061}, {\"ngram\": \"all young people\", \"from\": 4088, \"to\": 4104}, {\"ngram\": \"their background\", \"from\": 4120, \"to\": 4136}, {\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 4148, \"to\": 4156}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As mentioned a moment ago, the motion was ultimately defeated.\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4264, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A motion to repeal youth bail laws and anti-protest laws has been defeated at the NSW Labor conference.\", \"from\": 4266, \"to\": 4369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4352, \"end\": 4357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A motion\", \"from\": 4266, \"to\": 4274}, {\"ngram\": \"youth bail laws\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4300}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-protest laws\", \"from\": 4305, \"to\": 4322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As my colleagues reported yesterday, today's conference was the first time youth bail laws - passed by the state government earlier this year - were debated amongst party members.\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my colleagues\", \"from\": 4374, \"to\": 4387}, {\"ngram\": \"today's conference\", \"from\": 4408, \"to\": 4426}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4445}, {\"ngram\": \"youth bail laws\", \"from\": 4446, \"to\": 4461}, {\"ngram\": \"the state government\", \"from\": 4474, \"to\": 4494}, {\"ngram\": \"party members\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can read more on these laws below: The motion put forward today condemned the \\\"recent trend of Labor ... supporting legislation that erodes rather than advances civil liberties and human rights in our state\\\", calling for both the youth bail laws and anti-protest laws to be repealed.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4651, \"end\": 4656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these laws\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4582}, {\"ngram\": \"The motion\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4600}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"recent trend\", \"from\": 4629, \"to\": 4646}, {\"ngram\": \"supporting legislation\", \"from\": 4660, \"to\": 4682}, {\"ngram\": \"civil liberties\", \"from\": 4716, \"to\": 4731}, {\"ngram\": \"human rights\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4748}, {\"ngram\": \"our state\", \"from\": 4752, \"to\": 4761}, {\"ngram\": \"both the youth bail laws\", \"from\": 4776, \"to\": 4800}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-protest laws\", \"from\": 4805, \"to\": 4822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The motion also called for a charter of human rights to be enacted in the state.\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The motion\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4851}, {\"ngram\": \"a charter\", \"from\": 4868, \"to\": 4877}, {\"ngram\": \"human rights\", \"from\": 4881, \"to\": 4893}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mayor of Inner West council,Darcy Byrne, has been a vocal opponent of the laws and said they target First Nations children.\", \"from\": 4923, \"to\": 5050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4936, \"end\": 4954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inner_West_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Inner West council\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inner_West_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inner_West_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 4955, \"end\": 4960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Darcy\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.6392918296447843e-12, \"text\": \"Darcy\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Darcy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Darcy\"}, {\"begin\": 4961, \"end\": 4966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\", \"score\": 0.9999949750007379, \"rank\": 5.025023655556684e-06, \"text\": \"Byrne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\"}, {\"begin\": 5027, \"end\": 5040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indigenous_peoples_in_Canada\", \"score\": 0.8067924317200417, \"rank\": 0.23947617836024257, \"text\": \"First Nations\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indigenous_peoples_in_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indigenous_peoples_in_Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The mayor\", \"from\": 4923, \"to\": 4932}, {\"ngram\": \"a vocal opponent\", \"from\": 4977, \"to\": 4993}, {\"ngram\": \"the laws\", \"from\": 4997, \"to\": 5005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told the crowd that the policy of \\\"putting more juveniles in detention goes against the very ethos of the Uluru Statement from the Heart\\\": Whatever problem we think we are solving, this is not the answer.\", \"from\": 5051, \"to\": 5259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 5059, \"to\": 5068}, {\"ngram\": \"the policy\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5084}, {\"ngram\": \"more juveniles\", \"from\": 5097, \"to\": 5111}, {\"ngram\": \"detention\", \"from\": 5115, \"to\": 5124}, {\"ngram\": \"the very ethos\", \"from\": 5138, \"to\": 5152}, {\"ngram\": \"the Uluru Statement\", \"from\": 5156, \"to\": 5175}, {\"ngram\": \"the Heart\", \"from\": 5181, \"to\": 5190}, {\"ngram\": \"the answer\", \"from\": 5247, \"to\": 5257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are very deep and serious social and economic problems and disadvantages in remote communities, and youth crime is one symptom of that - one symptom of a much bigger problem that it's the Labor party's job to address, to overcome inequality and Indigenous injustice\\u2026 In the wake of the referendum, it's a kick in the guts for Aboriginal people to see the Labor party doing this.\", \"from\": 5260, \"to\": 5645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5454, \"end\": 5459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5511, \"end\": 5521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.5800275543277266, \"rank\": 0.5852149509726076, \"text\": \"Indigenous\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 5593, \"end\": 5610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.9967637638396804, \"rank\": 0.002225773844862139, \"text\": \"Aboriginal people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"very deep and serious social and economic problems\", \"from\": 5270, \"to\": 5320}, {\"ngram\": \"disadvantages\", \"from\": 5325, \"to\": 5338}, {\"ngram\": \"remote communities\", \"from\": 5342, \"to\": 5360}, {\"ngram\": \"youth crime\", \"from\": 5366, \"to\": 5377}, {\"ngram\": \"one symptom\", \"from\": 5381, \"to\": 5392}, {\"ngram\": \"that - one symptom\", \"from\": 5396, \"to\": 5414}, {\"ngram\": \"a much bigger problem\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5439}, {\"ngram\": \"inequality\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5506}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 5536, \"to\": 5544}, {\"ngram\": \"the referendum\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5562}, {\"ngram\": \"a kick\", \"from\": 5569, \"to\": 5575}, {\"ngram\": \"the guts\", \"from\": 5579, \"to\": 5587}, {\"ngram\": \"the Labor party\", \"from\": 5617, \"to\": 5632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no mandate from this conference for this policy.\", \"from\": 5646, \"to\": 5703, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no mandate\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5665}, {\"ngram\": \"this conference\", \"from\": 5671, \"to\": 5686}, {\"ngram\": \"this policy\", \"from\": 5691, \"to\": 5702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aboriginal leaders, the legal community, the human rights advocates and rank and file Labor party members do not support incarcerating more Aboriginal kids, and will fight against it to the end.\", \"from\": 5704, \"to\": 5898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5790, \"end\": 5795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5844, \"end\": 5854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.9951890886332877, \"rank\": 0.0031616415251127534, \"text\": \"Aboriginal\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Aboriginal leaders\", \"from\": 5704, \"to\": 5722}, {\"ngram\": \"the legal community\", \"from\": 5724, \"to\": 5743}, {\"ngram\": \"the human rights advocates\", \"from\": 5745, \"to\": 5771}, {\"ngram\": \"rank\", \"from\": 5776, \"to\": 5780}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5897}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were loud cheers in favour of, and against, the motion, but it was ultimately defeated.\", \"from\": 5900, \"to\": 5993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"loud cheers\", \"from\": 5911, \"to\": 5922}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 5926, \"to\": 5932}, {\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 5950, \"to\": 5960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We will bring you more from the speakers in response to the motion soon.\", \"from\": 5994, \"to\": 6066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the speakers\", \"from\": 6022, \"to\": 6034}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 6038, \"to\": 6046}, {\"ngram\": \"the motion\", \"from\": 6050, \"to\": 6060}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hello from Canberra whereAnthony Albanesehas just completed his much mooted ministry reshuffle.\", \"from\": 6068, \"to\": 6163, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Canberra\", \"from\": 6079, \"to\": 6087}, {\"ngram\": \"Albanesehas\", \"from\": 6101, \"to\": 6112}, {\"ngram\": \"his much mooted ministry reshuffle\", \"from\": 6128, \"to\": 6162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A couple of takeaways from the announcement: Albanese wants everyone to know that this is only occurring because two ministers,Brendan O'ConnorandLinda Burney, decided to step down from the frontbench ahead of their retirements at the next election and he is very focused on \\\"stability\\\".\", \"from\": 6165, \"to\": 6452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6210, \"end\": 6218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Albanese\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\"}, {\"begin\": 6317, \"end\": 6323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frances_Burney\", \"score\": 0.9997400245692104, \"rank\": 0.0002600291083465002, \"text\": \"Burney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frances_Burney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frances_Burney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"takeaways\", \"from\": 6177, \"to\": 6186}, {\"ngram\": \"the announcement\", \"from\": 6192, \"to\": 6208}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 6225, \"to\": 6233}, {\"ngram\": \"two ministers\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6291}, {\"ngram\": \"the frontbench\", \"from\": 6351, \"to\": 6365}, {\"ngram\": \"their retirements\", \"from\": 6375, \"to\": 6392}, {\"ngram\": \"the next election\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6413}, {\"ngram\": \"stability\", \"from\": 6441, \"to\": 6450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the days leading up to this announcement, Albanese has been keen to point out how few changes he has had to make up until this point.\", \"from\": 6454, \"to\": 6590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6499, \"end\": 6507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Albanese\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the days\", \"from\": 6457, \"to\": 6465}, {\"ngram\": \"this announcement\", \"from\": 6480, \"to\": 6497}, {\"ngram\": \"how few changes\", \"from\": 6535, \"to\": 6550}, {\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 6579, \"to\": 6589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today he said he had much the same team for \\\"two years and two months\\\" before this change.\", \"from\": 6591, \"to\": 6681, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"much the same team\", \"from\": 6612, \"to\": 6630}, {\"ngram\": \"two years\", \"from\": 6636, \"to\": 6645}, {\"ngram\": \"two months\", \"from\": 6650, \"to\": 6660}, {\"ngram\": \"this change\", \"from\": 6669, \"to\": 6680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the same time, there has been a need to reshuffle to reset the ministry - and some problem areas - ahead of the coming election.\", \"from\": 6683, \"to\": 6814, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 6686, \"to\": 6699}, {\"ngram\": \"a need\", \"from\": 6716, \"to\": 6722}, {\"ngram\": \"the ministry\", \"from\": 6745, \"to\": 6757}, {\"ngram\": \"some problem areas\", \"from\": 6764, \"to\": 6782}, {\"ngram\": \"the coming election\", \"from\": 6794, \"to\": 6813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That election can be held any time between now and May next year and it's obvious that Albanese wants focus to shift from some exposed weak spots with his government to the narrative on cost-of-living relief and the energy transition Labor is crafting.\", \"from\": 6815, \"to\": 7067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6902, \"end\": 6910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Albanese\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\"}, {\"begin\": 7049, \"end\": 7054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That election\", \"from\": 6815, \"to\": 6828}, {\"ngram\": \"now and May next year\", \"from\": 6858, \"to\": 6879}, {\"ngram\": \"focus\", \"from\": 6917, \"to\": 6922}, {\"ngram\": \"some exposed weak spots\", \"from\": 6937, \"to\": 6960}, {\"ngram\": \"his government\", \"from\": 6966, \"to\": 6980}, {\"ngram\": \"the narrative\", \"from\": 6984, \"to\": 6997}, {\"ngram\": \"living\", \"from\": 7009, \"to\": 7015}, {\"ngram\": \"the energy transition\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those portfolio weak spots - home affairs and immigration - have been tackled in this reshuffle by removing bothClare O'NeilandAndrew Giles, the ministers who held the portfolios, and installingTony Burketo both.\", \"from\": 7069, \"to\": 7281, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those portfolio weak spots - home affairs\", \"from\": 7069, \"to\": 7110}, {\"ngram\": \"immigration\", \"from\": 7115, \"to\": 7126}, {\"ngram\": \"this reshuffle\", \"from\": 7150, \"to\": 7164}, {\"ngram\": \"bothClare\", \"from\": 7177, \"to\": 7186}, {\"ngram\": \"O'NeilandAndrew Giles\", \"from\": 7187, \"to\": 7208}, {\"ngram\": \"the ministers\", \"from\": 7210, \"to\": 7223}, {\"ngram\": \"the portfolios\", \"from\": 7233, \"to\": 7247}, {\"ngram\": \"installingTony Burketo\", \"from\": 7253, \"to\": 7275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burke is one of Albanese's best-performing ministers and a long time ally: he will now carry the load of the government's troubles as senior minister in what are two troublesome areas, but he's been allowed to keep arts as a bit of a sweetner.\", \"from\": 7282, \"to\": 7525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7282, \"end\": 7287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edmund_Burke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.996736176887935e-29, \"text\": \"Burke\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edmund_Burke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edmund_Burke\"}, {\"begin\": 7298, \"end\": 7306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Albanese\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long time ally\", \"from\": 7339, \"to\": 7355}, {\"ngram\": \"the load\", \"from\": 7375, \"to\": 7383}, {\"ngram\": \"the government's troubles\", \"from\": 7387, \"to\": 7412}, {\"ngram\": \"senior minister\", \"from\": 7416, \"to\": 7431}, {\"ngram\": \"two troublesome areas\", \"from\": 7444, \"to\": 7465}, {\"ngram\": \"arts\", \"from\": 7497, \"to\": 7501}, {\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 7505, \"to\": 7510}, {\"ngram\": \"a sweetner\", \"from\": 7514, \"to\": 7524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burke will have two assistant ministers to help share the load, but it is going to be a challenge to keep across.\", \"from\": 7527, \"to\": 7640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7527, \"end\": 7532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edmund_Burke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.996736176887935e-29, \"text\": \"Burke\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edmund_Burke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edmund_Burke\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two assistant ministers\", \"from\": 7543, \"to\": 7566}, {\"ngram\": \"the load\", \"from\": 7581, \"to\": 7589}, {\"ngram\": \"a challenge\", \"from\": 7613, \"to\": 7624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"O'Neil has been moved into housing - another challenging area for the government, withJulie Collinsnow taking carriage of the portfolios she held in opposition: agriculture, forestry and fishing.\", \"from\": 7642, \"to\": 7837, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"O'Neil\", \"from\": 7642, \"to\": 7648}, {\"ngram\": \"housing - another challenging area\", \"from\": 7669, \"to\": 7703}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 7708, \"to\": 7722}, {\"ngram\": \"withJulie Collinsnow\", \"from\": 7724, \"to\": 7744}, {\"ngram\": \"carriage\", \"from\": 7752, \"to\": 7760}, {\"ngram\": \"the portfolios\", \"from\": 7764, \"to\": 7778}, {\"ngram\": \"opposition\", \"from\": 7791, \"to\": 7801}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a comfortable fit for a Tasmanian MP, but O'Neil will now have lead in negotiating with the Greens on housing policy, an area they have set up as an election battlefield.\", \"from\": 7838, \"to\": 8013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7935, \"end\": 7941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Greens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1711374636170332e-17, \"text\": \"Greens\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Greens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Greens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a comfortable fit\", \"from\": 7843, \"to\": 7860}, {\"ngram\": \"a Tasmanian MP\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7879}, {\"ngram\": \"O'Neil\", \"from\": 7885, \"to\": 7891}, {\"ngram\": \"lead\", \"from\": 7906, \"to\": 7910}, {\"ngram\": \"housing policy\", \"from\": 7945, \"to\": 7959}, {\"ngram\": \"an election battlefield\", \"from\": 7989, \"to\": 8012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"QueenslanderMurray Wattwas probably the biggest winner.\", \"from\": 8015, \"to\": 8070, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"QueenslanderMurray\", \"from\": 8015, \"to\": 8033}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest winner\", \"from\": 8051, \"to\": 8069}]}, {\