 \"from\": 10938, \"to\": 10959}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 10963, \"to\": 10970}, {\"ngram\": \"decisions\", \"from\": 10985, \"to\": 10994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are in the executive.\", \"from\": 10998, \"to\": 11024, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the executive\", \"from\": 11010, \"to\": 11023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What I have done with the envoy positions is put in place people who can give thought to things that might not lead to an immediate policy decision \\u2026 they are certainly not funding any programs.\", \"from\": 11025, \"to\": 11219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the envoy positions\", \"from\": 11047, \"to\": 11066}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 11077, \"to\": 11082}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 11083, \"to\": 11089}, {\"ngram\": \"thought\", \"from\": 11103, \"to\": 11110}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 11114, \"to\": 11120}, {\"ngram\": \"an immediate policy decision\", \"from\": 11144, \"to\": 11172}, {\"ngram\": \"any programs\", \"from\": 11206, \"to\": 11218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PM defends Labor record on immigration The PM has been asked about if Labor is better at managing immigration: What my job is to do is to make sure that we implement good policy.\", \"from\": 11221, \"to\": 11401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11232, \"end\": 11237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 11292, \"end\": 11297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PM\", \"from\": 11221, \"to\": 11223}, {\"ngram\": \"immigration\", \"from\": 11248, \"to\": 11259}, {\"ngram\": \"The PM\", \"from\": 11260, \"to\": 11266}, {\"ngram\": \"managing immigration\", \"from\": 11310, \"to\": 11330}, {\"ngram\": \"my job\", \"from\": 11337, \"to\": 11343}, {\"ngram\": \"good policy\", \"from\": 11387, \"to\": 11398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's what we have done, in spite of the rhetoric \\u2026 from the former government.\", \"from\": 11402, \"to\": 11482, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"spite\", \"from\": 11431, \"to\": 11436}, {\"ngram\": \"the rhetoric\", \"from\": 11440, \"to\": 11452}, {\"ngram\": \"the former government\", \"from\": 11460, \"to\": 11481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The truth is we have maintained border security.\", \"from\": 11484, \"to\": 11532, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The truth\", \"from\": 11484, \"to\": 11493}, {\"ngram\": \"border security\", \"from\": 11516, \"to\": 11531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The resources that have been allocated have never been higher than they are today.\", \"from\": 11533, \"to\": 11615, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The resources\", \"from\": 11533, \"to\": 11546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have made sure we have put in place Operation Sovereign Borders, [which] continues today.\", \"from\": 11616, \"to\": 11708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11655, \"end\": 11682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Operation_Sovereign_Borders\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Operation Sovereign Borders\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Operation_Sovereign_Borders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Operation_Sovereign_Borders\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 11649, \"to\": 11654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And what we have done as well [is] put in place a measure to reduce the migration numbers going forward.\", \"from\": 11710, \"to\": 11814, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 11752, \"to\": 11757}, {\"ngram\": \"a measure\", \"from\": 11758, \"to\": 11767}, {\"ngram\": \"the migration numbers\", \"from\": 11778, \"to\": 11799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was always going to be of course an uplift in numbers after the pandemic, after the borders that were shut were reopened.\", \"from\": 11815, \"to\": 11942, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 11847, \"to\": 11853}, {\"ngram\": \"an uplift\", \"from\": 11854, \"to\": 11863}, {\"ngram\": \"numbers\", \"from\": 11867, \"to\": 11874}, {\"ngram\": \"the pandemic\", \"from\": 11881, \"to\": 11893}, {\"ngram\": \"the borders\", \"from\": 11901, \"to\": 11912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PM defends scrapping assistant minister of the republic The PM has been asked why Labor have scrapped the republic as a portfolio (that wasMatt Thistlethwaite's portfolio).\", \"from\": 11944, \"to\": 12117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12027, \"end\": 12032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.765411707728242e-40, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PM\", \"from\": 11944, \"to\": 11946}, {\"ngram\": \"assistant minister\", \"from\": 11965, \"to\": 11983}, {\"ngram\": \"the republic\", \"from\": 11987, \"to\": 11999}, {\"ngram\": \"The PM\", \"from\": 12000, \"to\": 12006}, {\"ngram\": \"the republic\", \"from\": 12046, \"to\": 12058}, {\"ngram\": \"a portfolio\", \"from\": 12062, \"to\": 12073}, {\"ngram\": \"wasMatt Thistlethwaite's portfolio\", \"from\": 12080, \"to\": 12114}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said he inherited the position: I said before I was elected prime minister, I intended to have one referendum.\", \"from\": 12118, 